    <p>Entry timing matters. This page&rsquo;s thesis is structurally more compelling when bitcoin sits at or below long-term trend than when it sits in the upper band. Not a guarantee &mdash; the Power Law is a model, not a forecast &mdash; but the right honest guidance to surface before you choose a path.</p>

    <p>The Power Law channel describes bitcoin&rsquo;s long-term trajectory bounded by a trend line and a 0.42&times;&ndash;3&times; envelope. Bitcoin spends most of its time inside that channel, oscillating between phases of expensive (upper band) and cheap (around the floor). Entering near the floor means your forward CAGR is structurally larger; entering near the ceiling means it&rsquo;s structurally compressed. The math works in the long run from any reasonable entry, but how quickly it works depends on where in the channel you bought.</p>

