<section class="bvrp-section bvrp-methodology" id="methodology">
  <h2>Methodology &amp; <em>Sources</em></h2>

  <p>Every headline number on this page traces back to a specific source. Where the underlying number is a synthesis of multiple sources (rather than a single direct citation), it&rsquo;s flagged as such. The breakdown:</p>

  <details>
    <summary>Rental property economics &mdash; gross yields, waterfall, hidden costs, returns</summary>
    <ul class="source-list">
      <li><strong>Historical real returns (housing vs. equities, 1870&ndash;2015):</strong> <a href="https://www.frbsf.org/wp-content/uploads/wp2017-25.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&ldquo;The Rate of Return on Everything&rdquo;</a> (Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco / Jord&agrave;-Schularick-Taylor Macrohistory Database).</li>
      <li><strong>SFR Sharpe ratio of 1.14 (1986&ndash;2014):</strong> Demers &amp; Eisfeldt, <a href="https://anderson-review.ucla.edu/single-family-rentals/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&ldquo;Total Returns to Single-Family Rentals&rdquo;</a> (UCLA Anderson Review / Real Estate Economics).</li>
      <li><strong>St. Paul, MN $1.57B value loss:</strong> <a href="https://www.nber.org/system/files/working_papers/w30083/w30083.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&ldquo;Robbing Peter to Pay Paul?&rdquo;</a> (NBER Working Paper w30083).</li>
      <li><strong>Seattle 21% rental supply decline:</strong> <a href="https://www.seattle.gov/documents/departments/cityauditor/auditreports/rrioaudit.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Seattle City Auditor RRIO Program Audit</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Forced-sale liquidity discounts (6.6%&ndash;12.5%):</strong> Nielsen, &ldquo;Fire Sales and House Prices&rdquo; (Management Science).</li>
      <li><strong>Gross-to-net waterfall and the 50% Rule:</strong> CoreVest Finance maintenance-budgeting reference, plus NotebookLM synthesis combining property tax, insurance, management, and CapEx components.</li>
      <li><strong>Sweat equity (31 hours/month, $4,800/yr at $50/hr):</strong> Property118 landlord survey + valuation synthesis (modeled estimate).</li>
      <li><strong>19&ndash;33% total exit attrition:</strong> Compiled by combining academic fire-sale discounts (Nielsen) with industry-standard agent commissions and closing costs (modeled estimate).</li>
      <li><strong>11.7% leveraged ROI methodology critique:</strong> Property Scout 360 (industry-standard calculation methodology), NotebookLM synthesis of model inputs.</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Bitcoin yield instruments &mdash; STRC, SATA, CeFi, ETFs</summary>
    <ul class="source-list">
      <li><strong>Strategy preferred stock terms (STRF, STRC, STRK, STRD):</strong> SEC filings &mdash; Form 424B5 prospectuses and 8-K material event disclosures (corporate-issued, primary).</li>
      <li><strong>Strategy bitcoin treasury (843,706 BTC) and USD Reserve ($871M&ndash;$900M):</strong> Strategy 8-K filings as of late May 2026.</li>
      <li><strong>STRC&rsquo;s $1.7B annual obligation total:</strong> Derived from outstanding shares &times; dividend rate; verification pending against most recent Strategy 10-Q (modeled, primary source verification in progress).</li>
      <li><strong>Strive SATA structural details (13% rate, daily payments effective June 16 2026, 18-month reserve, 15,009 BTC, $50M STRC cross-holding):</strong> Strive Form 8-K / EX-99.1 SEC disclosure (corporate-issued, primary).</li>
      <li><strong>Return-of-Capital tax treatment:</strong> Tax counsel opinions filed in SEC prospectuses; the &ldquo;lack of accumulated earnings &amp; profits&rdquo; doctrine documented in Strategy&rsquo;s tax disclosures (corporate-issued).</li>
      <li><strong>Ledn S&amp;P-rated Issuer Trust 2026-1 Notes:</strong> S&amp;P Global Ratings Presale Report (third-party verified).</li>
      <li><strong>BlockFi and BlockFills bankruptcies:</strong> Kroll restructuring administration dockets and Sidley Austin legal analysis (third-party verified).</li>
      <li><strong>Trading volumes (STRC ~$350M daily, SATA ~$45.9M daily):</strong> BitcoinQuant exchange data dashboard (third-party verified).</li>
      <li><strong>Saylor &ldquo;$8,000 for 5 years&rdquo; doomsday threshold:</strong> Public statements from Strategy executive team; primary attribution verification in progress.</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Tax mechanics, HELOC, regulatory framings</summary>
    <ul class="source-list">
      <li><strong>Section 1031 like-kind treatment:</strong> <a href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/like-kind-exchanges-real-estate-tax-tips" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IRS guidance</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>HELOC interest deductibility under TCJA:</strong> IRS Publication 936 and related TCJA provisions.</li>
      <li><strong>Investment interest expense deduction (Schedule A):</strong> IRS Form 4952 instructions.</li>
      <li><strong>State-level capital gains and rent-control surfaces:</strong> Compiled from state revenue department publications and the NBER/legal-research summaries cited above.</li>
    </ul>
  </details>

